I live in a house. I am a hunter. I am not a great cook. I have friends who hunt. I live in a city now. I grew up on a farm. I have older brothers. I do not live in a city. I miss living in the countryside. I hunt deer and elk. I live in Oregon. I have a stuffed elk head. I have never hunted. I have never been to Oregon. I want to try bow hunting. I use rifles and shotguns to hunt. I own a 9mm handgun. I hunt birds and rabbits using a shotgun.,"Would you like to come over to my house and try some deer meat? Sure but I know how to hunt... can't say I know how cook. Wouldn't want to give you a bad first experience, but I'll try my best to make it tasty! My hunting buddies wife is a hell of a cook, pretty sure she could make dirt taste good! Speaking of good food, must have been nice having your father be a farmer. Fresh fruits and vegetables everyday sounds great. Sure was but it was hard work too. I cant remember a meal on the farm that I didnt earn! It is crazy how different life is now. Being in the city is way different. My older brothers make fun of me now calling me a city slicker! I can't imagine living in a city, no nature or anything. Don't you ever miss the good-ole farm life or are you happy to be a ""city slicker""? I miss the farm life for sure. I dont even get to really see deer here. I just happened to stumble upon a specialty meat shop. It must be nice for you to be able to just go out into nature whenever the mood strikes. Dont you have that hunting trip coming up? What was it your were going to hunt? Well, here in Oregon there's a lot to chose from to say the least. My usual is just Deer but every once in a blue moon I manage to get an Elk. My wife isn't super into hunting, but we do have a nice Elk head hanging in the living room! She must be very understanding! I have never gotten out that way but I imagine hunting can be fun. Being from the country I was the odd man out never having gone deer hunting but I have thought about trying it for quite some time. What do you use to hunt with? I like the idea of a compound bow but a nice rifle gives you more range. Yeah, i have a little 9 mm walther PPS M2. It is small enough to conceal but enough to get someone moving away from you! Do you have to use a certain slug for the elk? Like does a deer slug work for that or do you use the shotgun for other game?",test_403_2
I practice archery. I have a compound bow. I live in Oregon. I grew up on a farm. I've like hunting. I like beef. I love medium rare steak. I have tried eating deer body parts. I've stuffed a deer head before. I can shoot a pistol. I have experience with a shotgun.,"I found an archery range in the city where I can practice, so I went ahead and bought a compound bow. About $400, but still not a bad investment if I catch the bow hunting bug. I've never bow-hunted, but it sounds really hard. You need to come out to Oregon when you do catch the bug. We have tons of deer out here. Oh cool. I spent my childhood on a farm and can think of combining hunting with a farmstay in Oregon. I can see the satisfaction of hunting, but have to confess my preference for cattle fed in a less wild place! It's a much easier way to eat, I'll grant you that. Few things beat a medium rare steak. Of course, you don't get the satisfaction of being able to both eat and stuff the head of a cow. LOL. I haven't exactly tried eating deer head, but I have tried most other deer body parts -- can recommend the hindquarters. I have mixed thoughts about shouldering such a big shotgun that I think would be needed, even though a pistol is manageable for me! I totally understand that. But if you go out and shoot a bit before hunting, you'd get a real hang of the shotgun. But I'd love to learn to use the bow. I think you'd be in great shape using that instead of the shotgun!",test_403_3
I like cooking steak. I like watching Tiger King. I like to hunt and camp. I hunt elk. I like hunting with a bow and arrow. I live in Oregon.,"Yes, I had it on the weekend. I ate it while watching Tiger King. Have you seen it? I have not.  What's it about? I am planning to go hunting tomorrow. Thinking of camping out in the forest too.  I do like camping. Feels like I am one with nature. I think I will hunt an elk. Do you like camping? I do, especially when I can bring my bow and hunt.  Maybe we can go hunting together. I'd like to come visit you in oregon.  I've never been there and it would be a fun trip.",test_403_4
I like working on my father's blue pickup truck. I am a Mexican. I like meeting people. I have many friends. I like making friends over breakfast. I like poached eggs. I have a daughter. I have a daughter. I live on the 32nd floor of an apartment building. I do not have an elevator. I would rather live on the street than in an apartment. I work as a plumber. I want to buy a house.,"How do you do? Im working on my dads old blue pickup. Sure! We might finish in time to catch the sunset and a cervesa! I like meeting people a lot. I have so many friends. I meet most of my friends over breakfast in restaurants. Do you like poached eggs? Of course yes I do one of my daughter like making it. Yesterday my daughter made it all the way to the 32nd floor and dropped the eggs! I do not get that but I know I have a silly daughter too. I live up on the 32nd floor, in my apartment building and we have no elevator. That's some big exercise daily. I will rather live on the street.. Me too. Hopefully I get a raise as a plumber and we can move to a house.",test_405_1
"I am good at cooking arroz con pollo. I can cook mexican. I do not know what arroz con pollo is. my dish of arroz con pollo contains yellow rice, chicken thighs,  spices and sour cream on top. I want to try arroz con pollo. I am hungry. I also make tacos. I like breakfast burritos. I like breakfast burritos. I live in America. I like Mexican food. I like Chalupas. I think Taco Bell is a disgrace. I do not like Taco Bell.","My specialty is arroz con pollo! I will make it for you next time we get together. It has yellow rice, chicken thighs, and spices. I add sour cream on top. YUM! I make a mean taco too. I am getting hungry! I would like a good traditional Mexican dish. In America they consider Taco Bell Mexican food. I consider Taco Bell Dood Food, lol",test_405_2
I don't have much cooking experience. I know what spices to use to get the most flavor out of food. I don't often use herbs when cooking. I like cilantro. I would like some coaching with my cooking. I would be happy to instruct friends on how to cook. I'm familiar with cooking Mexican dishes. I like breakfast burritos. I like salsa and mushrooms in breakfast burritos. I do the grocery shopping.,"Yeah, you definitely want to spice it up a bit.  Cumin would add some good flavor and some onion and garlic powder as well.  I prefer fresh onion for this dish, but you can substitute the powder in a pinch.  Did you add any fresh herbs?. That's simple enough. Hey, how about you come over one of these nights and coach me? I'm kind of a mess so I think I need even more help. Sweet! I'm thinking you're already a master craftsman in the world of breakfast burritos. Any ideas for making one as tasty as possible? It never hurts to add some salsa to those burritos.  Mushrooms are tasty too, but really when it comes to something like that I think you can really just get creative and use all the ingredients you like/ Sounds good to me! I think I'll get extra crazy when I go grocery shopping and we can decide what to use from there. That's a good plan.  What time should I plan on visiting?",test_405_3
My dad is still alive. I know at least two recipes. I have a son and a family. I have a job that relates working on a truck. I know how to drive. I know how to drive. I live in a town. I have at least two kids. I like tacos. I am on vacation with my family.,"I tried out the recipe you showed me the other day with my Dad. He told me it was great and couldn't believe I cooked it! I ended up making those burritos with the mushrooms and the salsa and all that. It was so fresh and so good! Yes, he did! He loved it too. You'll have to show me another recipe the next time you're over. My family can't get enough! I make a simple black bean and corn salsa that goes perfect on the side of everything I cook but I'll get to that later. How is the work on the truck coming along?  That would be wonderful! I can't wait until we can take her out for a drive. You know, there are some great taco stands around. I'll have to show you! There's also a beautiful park downtown where the kids could run around and play. I'd love to show you!",test_405_4
"I love animals. I love hiking. I like animals. I used to be a veterinarian but I quit. I like to travel. I love the outdoors. I am in love with my neighbor, John, and nobody knows. I am a singer and a blogger. I care about equality. I care about protecting animals. I am a vegan. I do not vote. I like to travel abroad. I would like to travel abroad. I trekked in Japan. I love traveling.","Well I love to hike so I enjoy the random animals I sometimes see.. I love outdoors, too. That's why I quit being a veterinarian, so I can travel more. What? Do, tell! I'll tell you mine, too. Im actually in love with my neighbor john. Dont tell!. Ohhh, okay! I am a singer now...and a blogger. If I were to be political, I'd sing for protecting animals. I keep vegan diet, even! That's great! Id vote for you, if I voted, but I don't.. Haha, thanks! Another thing I love is traveling abroad. Wow, I would love traveling abroad so I could hike everywhere.. Yes, it's awesome! I even trekked in japan. How fun! I love traveling, it humbles me and keeps me kind.",test_407_1
I recently rescued a kitten. One of my acquaintances is called John. I have feelings for someone named John. I go hiking sometimes.,"I was walking down the road and came across a poor, shivering kitten in a box. Naturally, I picked him up and took him home! He's only about 5 weeks old and I'm trying to get him to eat something. I think I might have to take him to the vet because he keeps making this wheezing sound.  Yes, there is no way I could have left him, I am happy to give him a home. Have you ever rescued an animal? I never have.  It would break my heart if I seen one needing rescuing. oh, I forgot I told you about him last time we spoke. I try not to tell others about him. No, I haven't talked to him :( I don't know. I need something from him that he feels the same about me. yea, but it is scary because he may not feel the same as I do and then nothing, not even hope I was thinking about that, mentioning I am going on a hike and would he like to join me",test_407_2
"I have a kitten. I have a sofa. I had a cat named Gracie when I was younger. I love animals. I am passionate about animal rights. I think killing animals for food is wrong. I am vegan. I used to be a vegetarian, but I am not anymore.","My kitten is growing up so fast, the other day she managed to jump up onto a the sofa for the first time.  Not really to be honest. I mostly just enjoy playing with her because she's so darn cute! Have you ever had a cat? I did have a cat when I was younger.  Her name was Gracie and she would actually fetch paintbrushes if you threw it across the room for her! Oh my gosh that's so cute! I just love animals. I always have since I was a little kid. I used to hold mock protests about animal rights and abuse with my friends. That is AWESOME! I love to hear about kids getting involved in their passions early in life.  Have you been a vegan since you were a kid as well? My parents used to make me eat meat and stuff when I was really little but I put on a presentation about animal rights and how it was wrong to kill them for food and they accepted that I was serious and let me live my lifestyle. I'd say I was about 11 when that happened. Have you ever gone vegan? I was a vegetarian when I was younger but never thought about fully going vegan. That was a while ago, it seems like within the last 5-10 years there have been so many new products on the market that would make going vegan a lot easier. There is a ton of stuff out there to help people whether they are seasoned or new to the life. I definitely recommend taking a look at all the items on the market. So how's John?",test_407_3
I'm scared of rejection. I think there is another woman. I believe John is a pediatrician. I think John is really handsome. I don't believe John is not seeing other women. My life is dull.,"I have but I'm really nervous.  I'm scared to get rejected! There was a woman that would come over all the time a while ago but I haven't seen her in a year or so. Okay, that's a good sign for you and it probably means he's not gay. What does he do for work? He's a doctor.  I believe he's a pediatrician. He's the most handsome guy I've ever seen in my entire life. Maybe he keeps a secret apartment for that type of stuff! This is all very exciting for me. My life is so, so dull!",test_407_4
I have a kite. I work in a pizza shop. I am a zookeeper. I have a pet raccoon. I have a bearded dragon. I prefer baseball to football. I am a huge fan of Dallas Cowboy. I go to college. I no longer go to school. I live with my grandparents.,"I just got home from work, I smell like pepperoni. I work in pizza shop. Oh cool! I am a zookeeper at the zoo.. Wow now that sounds much funner than my job. Wanna trade? Sure as long as my bearded dragon and pet raccoon can hang out there! Yes but I like baseball more. I am a huge fan of the dallas cowboys!!! I'm so sorry. No one really voted to pick america's team, you know?? Haha. No, I'm long gone from there. Lucky! Im living with my grandparents, in college, and trying to pay bills. The bills never end, I'm afraid!",test_409_1
I work at a zoo. I like giraffes. I have not worked with giraffes before. I recently started working with a giraffe named Charlie. I am studying to be an accountant. I am not good at doing taxes. I enjoy eating salads. I have grandparents who are still alive. My grandparents are all deceased. I live with my grandparents. I used to watch baseball with my grandparents. I am a fan of the Dallas Cowboys.,"My work at the zoo just got a new animal! I know!!  The Giraffe's name is Charlie. I love giraffes. They are so beautiful to watch. They seem so chill and mellow. He absolutely is.  I am excited to get to work with him.  I've never really worked with giraffes before.  How's school going? They love to eat lettuce. Bring him lettuce and you will be fast friends. School is going great! I think I will make a great accountant when I am done. I love salads so he is in good company.  We can share my lunch!  Accounting seems like a good plan.  I struggle doing my taxes so I could use your help!  Once I have my CPA, I sure will! My grandparents are most excited about the help with their taxes too :) I am so grateful to be able to live with them and spend so much quality time with them. How old were you when yours passed? By the time I was 17, they had all passed.  Luckily I was able to spend a lot of time with them during my childhood.  We used to watch Yankee games together, Do they also like the Cowboys? They are huge Cowboys fans. They got me into the team!",test_409_2
I have a pet raccoon. I have a pet named Charlie. Charlie is a giraffe. I share my salads with the giraffe. I work at the zoo.,"I made a video of my pet racoon for you. I'll send you a link. I'd like to see that.  How old is Charlie? I think that would be OK.  I would prefer not to have an encounter with  the giraffe's teeth though.  Is it safe to fee them? About four months. I often give Charlie some of my salads haha. I bet he likes that quite a lot.  Does the zoo have any friends for Charlie or is he the only giraffe they keep? Just Charlie. Sadly, we can't take on any more giraffes unless we find one to rescue. That's rare though.",test_409_3
"I enjoy hearing about giraffes. I am not a high energy person. I take care of giraffes. I take care of all of the safari animals. Hawks or eagles are my favorite animals, but I like all birds. I work at the zoo. I don't work directly with birds. Bearded dragons are my favorite animals. I don't know a lot about bearded dragons.","He started running laps around his habitat! I wish I had that much energy!! He just eat's acacia leaves and I am pretty sure they are poisonous to humans! Maybe it's something in the water! We have lots of animals! I only work with the safari animals though! What's your favorite animal? I have always loved birds, especially birds of prey. Probably hawks or eagles. That's super cool! We have both of those at the zoo but I don't work with them directly! I would say a bearded dragon would be my favorite for sure!",test_409_4
I go to college. I'm taking summer courses. I have outstanding student loans. I work too much to do anything fun. I teach jiu-jitsu to kids. I'm allergic to dairy. I like meat. I like seafood. I like sushi.,"Hi. I'm a college student, what do you do for a living.. I work in it. It takes up all my time. Even when I'm at home, I'm only thinking about work. Okay. I'm going to take summer courses so I can graduate early.. I should have done that. I could have avoided some of the student loans I am paying. Student loan is the worst. My hobby is martial arts, what your hobby. I'm too busy with work for hobbies, but I like listening to black sabbath. Okay. I like to teach kids jiu-jitsu. For 5 years now. I'm allergic to dairy product. Are you allergic to anything.. No, I can eat anything. My favorite food is meat. What is yours? I like seafood too, especially sushi. I don't go to restaurants though since I am in debt.",test_411_1
I work a lot of hours. I enjoy sushi. I like california rolls. I like sushi. My favorite is salmon or tuna. I prefer cooked sushi to raw. I enjoy raw sushi. My job is not stressful. I am a poor college student. I have student loans.,"Oh you know, the same as usual, good but wow, too many hours! I managed to go out one night for sushi, but it was brief and alone Well, at least you went out. That's a good start. What kind of sushi did you have? A california roll, I like to get that once in a while. Maybe if I get a day off from work we can go out and get some sushi together That sounds like a plan! My favorite sushi is salmon or tuna. I'm not too adventurous when it comes to sushi. A California roll is a good one. I like those, too. Yeah I don't always eat raw sushi, i like the cooked options as well, like smoked salmon with avocado! Yum! I do like the raw salmon and tuna, though. When it's good, it just melts in your mouth. Gosh, now I'm hungry for sushi!  It's not too stressful no, it's just a ton of hours but I agree to do it because I enjoy saving moneyt Yep, money is good to have. Ha! Being a poor college student doesn't leave me many opportunities to save money. I hear that, I'm still debating whether or not i want to pay back the student loans",test_411_2
I need a better work-life balance. I want to pay my debt. I am young. Maybe I should take a class about making sushi. I didn't have very good luck making sushi. I worry about bacteria on raw fish. I prefer cooked fish.,"Lenders will typically work with you on repayment plans for student loans. It's better to make small payments than no payments at all.  That makes sense. The lenders want to know that I'm trying to settle my debt. I need to find a better work-life balance though. I want to pay the debt, but I don't want to spend all my time working for the ""man."" Especially while I'm young. If I won the lottery, I would just pay off the debt. I wouldn't stop working. I don't hate working, just working all the time. LOL after my first go at it I'd agree that ten classes would do the trick! The rice is what seemed the trickiest.  And not overloading the roll, which was my struggle.  Gotcha. It's not as simple as making a sandwich. Can't just load it up with everything and hope for the best. I worry about bacteria on the fish. I prefer the cooked stuff because it seems safer. I have tried the raw stuff, but I didn't feel so good after.",test_411_3
"I prefer chicken. I love lamb and lamb chops. I like bacon, it is a great breakfast meat. I like chicken sausage more than regular sausage. I don't like bacon. I prefer pork sausage. I do not like chicken sausage. I like fish. I have not fished before. I do not like raw fish. I eat sushi and tuna. I like sushi. I cannot make sushi.","I think I prefer chicken to anything as it is so versatile. What about you? I like bacon because it is salty. Great breakfast meat I think. What are your thoughts on sausages? I don't know, there is something about bacon i don't like might be because of their feed. I like sausages but the ones made with chicken. You should try those. they have that salty taste you like. Strangely enough I am not a fan of chicken sausage. Prefer pork sausage. Maybe you just aren't a fan of pork overall.  No still not a fan of raw fish but have got plans to go fishing with my friend on the weekend. It will be the first time and I am kind of looking forward to it. Have you been fishing before? That is great. I hope you get to eat sushi. No, i guess i have to do fishing at some point because of the sushi and tuna i used to eat. Have you tried tuna rolls ? Yes, I tried tuna rolls one. I like sushi but still a little reluctant. Maybe after fishing and a sushi making lesson I will be better. Can you make sushi?",test_411_4
I am struggling to pay my bills. My travel bills are very expensive. I am know an opera singer. I quit working as a vet. I love my job. I cannot think of another job I would like to do. I blog about animals and vegan recipes. I eat meat every day. I am a vegan. I used to eat meat until I watched a documentary. I am currently working for the Russians. I am an Astronaut.,"Could be better. Just got my bills pretty expensive. I feel you there, traveling has been rewarding but very expensive, even if for work. I used to work as a vet, but quit a few years back an sing opera. Cool I love my job and sometimes I cant think a bout anything else. Understandable, I also blog about animals and vegan recipes, im pretty passionate. Wow vegan that must be tough I cant go a day without meat. I was the same way until a certain documentary broke me. Lol what do you do? I am a astronaut I work for the russians.",test_414_1
I have visited Australia. I went to the Sydney Opera House. My favorite animal is the Koala. I held a Koala named Pansy. I like Koalas. I have been to outer space. I am a vegetarian.,"Oh, I think probably Australia. The animals are amazing, and you know I visited the Opera House. I'm sure it doesn't compare to outer space though! That sounds fantastic! I would love to go to Australia! The koala has always been my favorite animal, but I'd never seen one in real life until I went. I actually got to hold one at a zoo. Her name was Pansy. I was a little worried about mistreatment for tourist money, but Pansy seemed to have a pretty kushy life.  Yes, but they can be quite fierce when they need to. I relate. Their claws are quite weaponous. That isn't really a word, but it should be. Be sure to give me a heads up if you hear from the Russians that it may be better if I permanently relocate Down Under. I had a dream last night that I was eating steak! Me! I can't decide if it was my subconscious telling me to eat some meat or if I should just file it under Nightmares. ",test_414_2
I want to travel to Egypt. I like to travel. I am impressed by architecture. I've been to outer space. I've been on a spaceship. I want to go to space. I am interested in advertisements about space. I am familiar with game shows. I feel like a lucky person in contests.,"I think i will try Egypt. I have good things about it. I think it would be pretty cool to see a pyramid.  Absolutely incredible. Putting my finger to the glass and being able to cover up the entire earth was so surreal. And to be one of the few people in history to go into space was such an honor. There's talk of being able to go on a space vacation in our lifetime, but I do not know how realistic that actually is. That would be very cool though! I would be the first one to book! We can only hope that something like that could come in our lifetime I would be so interesting to see advertisements on YouTube or tv about taking a vacation in space. I can only imagine the cost! It's going to be crazy! I could do that! I feel like I have a good chance at winning one of those games",test_414_3
i have been to space before. I have been asked to go again. I will go to space again. I am interested in traveling. i am out of shape. I will go to space next year. I am a vegan. I am not a good cook.,"I've been asked to board the next shuttle to space again.  I could probably make more money staying on Earth and doing stuff like talks at events, but I really can't pass up an opportunity to be a part f another shuttle launch. I hope that in the future it is easier for the average person to experience it. That truly is a once in a lifetime opportunity! And for you, now twice! I think space travel will become more attainable pretty soon. I know some companies are trying to make that happen. Well if you need some vegan recipes for your diet, I can help with that! I don't know much about space, but I know my health food. I could defiantly use some meal ideas. I really like to cook, but I've never really been very good at it though. Any simple to make meals come to your mind?",test_414_4
"I have 2 kids. I have dogs. I love taking naps. My kids are 5 and 3. I like taking naps. My favorite food is burger and fries. I like eating fast food while I paint. I learned how to paint a little while in school. I went to school in Spain. I inherited my parents movie theater. I work a government job. I like scary movies. I like scary movies. I have two dogs, their names are Bounty and Snickers. My favorite type of music is Country.","Hey. Sorry, just put my 2 kids to bed. What's new? Its okay, just chillin with my dogs. How old are your kid? I like naps too, especially after eating my favorite, burgers and fries. That'll do it. I like eating fast food while I paint. I did a little painting at school in spain. Nice. I paint but I also really like avery movies. Where do you work? As the only child, I took over my parents movie theater. Cool. I meant scary. Silly auto correct. To think I work in government too. Jeez. I like scary movies too, my dogs bounty & snickers keep me company lol. What kind of music do you like? Country is my favorite.",test_416_1
